## Basic Command Structure

```tsx
import { List, ActionPanel, Action, Icon } from "@raycast/api";

export default function Command() {
  return (
    <List>
      <List.Item
        title="Hello World"
        subtitle="Raycast Extension"
        actions={
          <ActionPanel>
            <Action
              title="Open"
              onAction={() => console.log("Action triggered")}
            />
          </ActionPanel>
        }
      />
    </List>
  );
}
```

## Development Workflow

### Start Development Server

```bash
npx ray develop
```

- Hot-reloading enabled
- Error messages in Raycast window
- Console logs visible in terminal

### Build Extension

```bash
npx ray build -e dist
```

### Lint Code

```bash
npx ray lint
```

## Command Modes

### View Mode (Default)

```tsx
import { List } from "@raycast/api";

export default function Command() {
  return <List />;
}
```

### No-View Mode

```json
{
  "mode": "no-view"
}
```

```tsx
import { showToast, Toast } from "@raycast/api";

export default async function Command() {
  await showToast({
    style: Toast.Style.Success,
    title: "Task completed",
  });
}
```

## Key Concepts

- **Commands**: Individual actions users can trigger
- **Views**: UI components (List, Grid, Detail, Form)
- **Actions**: User interactions (copy, open, etc.)
- **Preferences**: User-configurable settings
- **Cache**: Temporary data storage
- **Storage**: Persistent data storage
- **OAuth**: Authentication flows

